track_notes: It is a long way to drive from Nice, the last 10km are on a small mountain road, you will drive on a funny bridge! the walk to summit it easy and plenty path may be used. Not so much room on summit, but enought for an inverted V.

Plenty room to park at the Col de St Leger, when snow is on the forest road it is better to follow that way. The last part might be sleepy and the sloope is hard. Nice panorama on summit, not many room! enought for a vertical or small inverted v dipole
This is a long way to this summit, nearly 3 hours walk up and 2h30mn down. the path is good enought. You can park along the small road to Agnerc (1 or 2 places) No much room on summit for antenna.
